<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Recipe 2: Lentil Soup</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>
    <div class="container">
      <img
        src="/images/lentil-soup.jpg"
        alt="Lentil Soup"
        class="recipe-image"
      />
      <h1>Lentil Soup</h1>
      <p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>1 cup dry lentils, rinsed</li>
        <li>1 medium onion, chopped</li>
        <li>2 carrots, sliced</li>
        <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
        <li>1 can diced tomatoes (14 oz)</li>
        <li>4 cups vegetable broth</li>
        <li>2 cups water</li>
        <li>1 tsp cumin</li>
        <li>1 tsp paprika</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric</li>
        <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
        <li>Fresh parsley for garnish</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Instructions:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>Heat a large pot over medium heat and add a little olive oil.</li>
        <li>
          Sauté onions, carrots, and garlic until softened (about 5 minutes).
        </li>
        <li>
          Add cumin, paprika, turmeric, salt, and pepper. Stir for 1 minute.
        </li>
        <li>
          Add diced tomatoes, lentils, vegetable broth, and water. Stir well.
        </li>
        <li>
          Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let it simmer for 30-35 minutes,
          or until lentils are tender.
        </li>
        <li>Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.</li>
        <li>Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley.</li>
      </ol>
      <a href="/">⬅️ Back to Home</a>
    </div>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  </body>
</html>
